<p>BRIDLE</p>
<p>frenum is the bridle with which the rider breaks the wild horse.</p>
<p>habena is the rein with which he turns the obedient horse.</p>
<p>oreae was perhaps the generic term for bridle and reins.</p></note></bibl>
